main event: A civilian reported seeing a bright, circular object that hovered and moved around near his home in West Alexandria, Ohio on January 9, 1960.
interesting points: The object appeared to be approximately 130 degrees southeast of compass north (just a cheap compass) at around 2 o'clock.
The object was last seen around 6:12 AM.
The witness did not believe in 'flying saucer stories' but felt there must be an explanation for what he saw.
The Air Force requested that the witness complete a questionnaire for further analysis and evaluation.
The Air Force acknowledged the report but stated that the information provided was insufficient for a valid conclusion.
